{
  "id": "41579eafac0a41c99c1fb39ee89d503b",
  "title": "A.P.T.S. Partial Targeting",
  "description": "Assisted Partial Targeting System (A.P.T.S.). Tactical dismemberment.",
  "longDescription": "<p>Preview: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;RvgdtxGYG8c\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v&#61;RvgdtxGYG8c</a></p><p>Documentation: <a href=\"http://genmindo.com/apts\" rel=\"nofollow\">genmindo.com/apts</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Assisted Partial Targeting System allows tactical targeting of the body </p><p>parts with dismemberment. </p><p><br /></p><p>Features: </p><p>* slow motion with smooth auto targeting; </p><p>* accuracy calculations based on obstructions, including other body parts; </p><p>* special action for misses and critical strikes with switching to side </p><p>view; </p><p>* works with moving characters and meshes in sockets; </p><p>* any custom combinations of body parts; </p><p><br /></p><p>Similar to &#34;CharacterMovement Component&#34;, the &#34;A.P.T.S. Component&#34; allows </p><p>to achieve quick setup for new characters, since the whole logic is </p><p>implemented into character automatically after linking hotkey events. </p><p>Everything is done with Blueprints, no C&#43;&#43; involved. Commented code with </p><p>categorized functions. </p><p><br /></p><p>forum support thread: <a href=\"https://forums.unrealengine.com/showthread.php?133999-A-P-T-S-Assisted-Partial-Targeting-and-Dismemperment-system\" rel=\"nofollow\">forums.unrealengine.com/showthread.php?133999-A-P-T-S-Assisted-Partial-Targeting-and-Dismemperment-system</a></p>",
  "technicalDetails": "Blueprints: <br />1 Actor Component Blueprint <br />5 Character Blueprints <br />1 Data Table <br />1 Projectile Blueprint <br />1 HUD <br />5 Widgets <br />2 Structures <br />2 Enum <br />Number of characters: 3 <br />Intended Platform: Windows, Linux, OSX <br />Platforms Tested: Windows, Linux",
